flex property

1. flex-direction : The flex-direction property defines in which direction the container wants to stack the flex items.
2. flex-wrap : The flex-wrap property specifies whether the flex items should wrap or not.
3. flex-flow : The flex-flow property is a shorthand property for setting both the flex-direction and flex-wrap properties.
4. justify-content : The justify-content property is used to align the flex items.
5. align-items : The align-items property is used to align the flex items vertically.
6. align-content : The align-content property is used to align the flex lines.